-- Willis Group Names Krauze Its North America Chief as Bailey Leaves Company
-- B y   N a t a l i e   D o s s   a n d   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 2010-11-22T21:24:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/willis-group-names-krauze-its-north-america-chief-as-bailey-leaves-company.html
Willis Group Holdings Plc, the
world’s third-largest insurance broker, said  Vic Krauze  will
replace  Don Bailey  as chief executive officer of North American
operations.  Bailey will leave the company, the Dublin, Ireland-based
insurance broker said today in a statement distributed by
Business Wire. Bailey will join Allstate Corp., Insurance
Insider reported today. Krauze was previously chief operating
officer at Willis North America.  Chief Executive Officer  Joseph Plumeri  is expanding in the
U.S. and taking on larger rivals Aon Corp. and Marsh & McLennan
Cos. in the brokerage business. The company bought Hilb Rogal
and Hobbs Co. in Glen Allen, Virginia, in 2008 for $1.7 billion.  “Vic brings to this role great knowledge of our
business,” Plumeri said in the statement. “We thank Don for
his many contributions to our firm and wish him all the best.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
